---
<LandingLayout
  title="Auto Detailing Website Design with Quote Systems | Designed to Elevate"
  description="Detailing and ceramic coating shop websites with a real quote system — prices the job by vehicle, captures the lead before they bounce, and texts the quote to your phone to book. See the Fitchin build."
  pathname="auto-detailing-websites"
  noindex={true}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <BreadcrumbSchema items={[
    { name: 'Home', url: `${SITE}/` },
    { name: 'Auto Detailing Websites', url: `${SITE}/auto-detailing-websites` },
  ]} />

  <main>
    <!-- FIXED HERO BACKGROUND — pinned to the viewport with position:fixed so it
         stays still while content scrolls over it (works on iOS Safari, which
         ignores background-attachment:fixed). Sits at z-0; the hero below is
         transparent to reveal it, and everything after the hero is wrapped in an
         opaque bg-bg layer that scrolls over the top of it. -->
    <div class="fixed inset-0 z-0 pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/auto-detail/detailing-bay-hero.jpg?v=2"
        alt=""
        class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover"
        width="1672"
        height="941"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-bg/45"></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-bg/75 via-bg/32 to-bg/12"></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-bg/15 via-transparent to-bg"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <div id="top" class="relative z-10 overflow-hidden border-b border-line">

      <!-- MINIMAL LANDING HEADER — no nav, transparent over the hero. -->
      <header class="relative z-30 w-full">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-4 sm:py-5 flex items-center justify-between gap-3 sm:gap-4">
          <a href="#top" class="flex items-center" aria-label="Designed to Elevate">
            <img
              src="/logo-wordmark-orange.png"
              alt="Designed to Elevate"
              width="320"
              height="96"
              class="h-8 sm:h-10 w-auto"
            />
          </a>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 sm:gap-3">
            <a href={QUOTE_HREF} class="btn-ghost !border-accent !text-accent !py-2.5 !px-3.5 sm:!px-4 !text-[0.78rem] sm:!text-[0.85rem] whitespace-nowrap">
              Build My Estimate
              <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- HERO CONTENT -->
      <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8 pt-6 sm:pt-10 pb-14 sm:pb-20">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] gap-10 lg:gap-14 items-center">
          <div>
            <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Auto Detailing Websites</span>
            <h1 class="mt-5 text-[2.2rem] sm:text-[2.9rem] lg:text-[3.3rem] leading-[1.04] font-bold tracking-tight">
              Auto detailing websites that turn ad clicks into <span class="text-accent">priced quotes</span> — before the customer calls another shop.
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-6 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] sm:text-[1.1rem] leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              We build fast, mobile-first websites for detail shops with a real quote system built in — so customers choose their service, vehicle, condition, and ceramic tier, then send a priced quote straight to your phone to book. You own the code, the site, and the setup outright.
            </p>

            <!-- HERO PROOF ELEMENT — live-in-production badge + named shop. Real proof beats a tagline here. -->
            <div class="mt-5 inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 rounded-full border border-line bg-surface-1/60 px-3 py-1.5">
              <span class="relative flex h-1.5 w-1.5" aria-hidden="true">
                <span class="absolute inline-flex h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-accent/60 animate-ping"></span>
                <span class="relative inline-flex rounded-full h-1.5 w-1.5 bg-accent"></span>
              </span>
              <span class="font-display text-[0.75rem] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-text-soft">Live in Production · Built for Fitchin Auto Detail</span>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href={QUOTE_HREF} data-hero-cta class="btn-primary">
                Build My Ballpark Estimate
                <span class="text-[0.85em] font-normal opacity-80">→ 60 sec</span>
              </a>
              <a href="#case-study" class="btn-ghost">
                See the Fitchin Build
                <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-3 text-[0.85rem] text-text-muted">
              No spam, no pushy sales call. Bill replies within 24 hours.
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 text-[0.9rem] text-text-muted">
              Quote system included &nbsp;·&nbsp; You own the code &nbsp;·&nbsp; No required monthly
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute -inset-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-accent/30 via-accent/5 to-transparent rounded-[2rem] blur-3xl opacity-60"></div>
            <div class="relative card overflow-hidden max-w-[20rem] mx-auto">
              <div class="relative aspect-[9/16] bg-surface-2 overflow-hidden">
                <img
                  src="/showcase/fitchin-mobile.png"
                  alt="Fitchin Auto Detail mobile homepage — heat, glare, and ceramic protection messaging with a 'See your price in 2 min' quote button."
                  class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-top"
                  width="1320"
                  height="2678"
                  loading="lazy"
                  decoding="async"
                />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONTENT OVER THE FIXED BACKGROUND — opaque bg-bg so the hero photo only
         shows behind the hero, then this layer scrolls up over it. -->
    <div class="relative z-10 bg-bg">

    <!-- MINI PROOF BAR — condensed teaser of the live Fitchin PageSpeed scores.
         Full scoreboard still lives in the case study; this is the 10-second
         "we measure this" signal up top, before the pain section. -->
    <div class="border-b border-line bg-surface-1/30">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-5 sm:py-6">
        <div class="flex items-center flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2">
          <span class="font-display text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent whitespace-nowrap">Live Fitchin build</span>
          <div class="flex items-center flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1 text-[0.92rem] text-text">
            <span><span class="font-display font-bold text-accent">98</span> Performance</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span><span class="font-display font-bold text-accent">100</span> SEO</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span><span class="font-display font-bold text-accent">100</span> Best Practices</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span><span class="font-display font-bold text-accent">97</span> Accessibility</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-1.5 text-[0.92rem] text-text-soft">Fast pages waste fewer paid clicks.</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-[0.72rem] text-text-muted italic">Measured with Google PageSpeed Insights, May 2026. Scores can shift over time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAIN -->
    <section class="relative border-b border-line">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 sm:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> The Problem</span>
          <h2 class="mt-5 text-[1.9rem] sm:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.07] font-bold">
            Most detail-shop websites describe the work. They can't price it — so they hand every quote back to your phone.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
            A generic contact form is a tax on your day. Every job that could have been priced online instead becomes phone tag — and most customers won't wait.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
          {painCards.map((c) => (
            <div class="card p-7 flex flex-col gap-3">
              <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-[1.05rem] leading-snug text-text">{c.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-text-soft leading-relaxed">{c.body}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OLD WAY vs NEW WAY — contrast block. Justifies costing more than a $500 template. -->
    <section class="relative border-b border-line bg-surface-1/30">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 sm:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Old vs. New</span>
          <h2 class="mt-5 text-[1.9rem] sm:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.07] font-bold">
            A normal website vs. a quote system.
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
            Both cost money to run. Only one of them prices the work and captures the lead.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
          <div class="card p-7 sm:p-8 flex flex-col">
            <div class="font-display text-[0.74rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-text-muted mb-4">A normal website</div>
            <ul class="space-y-3 flex-1">
              {oldWay.map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[0.98rem] text-text-soft leading-snug">
                  <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-text-muted/15 text-text-muted flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
                    <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
                  </span>
                  <span>{item}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card p-7 sm:p-8 flex flex-col border-accent/40 bg-accent/[0.04]">
            <div class="font-display text-[0.74rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent mb-4">A Designed to Elevate quote system</div>
            <ul class="space-y-3 flex-1">
              {newWay.map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[0.98rem] text-text leading-snug">
                  <span class="mt-1 inline-flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent/20 text-accent flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">
                    <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
